  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Boil a full kettle</p><p>Add the<strong> bulgur</strong> to a heatproof bowl with 200ml <span class=\"text-danger\">[350ml]</span><strong> boiled water</strong> and the <strong>chicken stock mix</strong></p><p>Pour in the <strong>beetroot</strong> <strong>juice</strong> from the packet, cover and set aside</p><p>Tip: The beetroot juice will turn your bulgur bright pink!</p>",
      "order": 1,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1612880255607-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1612880255607-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1612880255607-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1612880255607-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1612880255607-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, add most of the<strong> ground sumac</strong> (save a pinch for garnish!),<strong> soy sauce </strong>and<strong> half </strong>of the<strong> pomegranate molasses </strong>(save the rest for later!) to a plate with a generous grind of <strong>pepper </strong>and mix it together</p><p>Add the <strong>chicken breasts </strong>and turn until well coated</p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1612880274598-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1612880274598-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1612880274598-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1612880274598-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1612880274598-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with a drizzle of <strong>olive oil </strong>over a medium-high heat</p><p>Once hot, add the<strong> coated chicken </strong>and cook for 6-7 min on each side or until cooked through (no pink meat!) – this is your <strong>pomegranate</strong> <strong>chicken</strong></p>",
